BT 1 0 0 1 54 329.6 Tm (healthy adult brains.) Tj T* ET
BT /F3 10 Tf 12 TL ET
BT 1 0 0 1 54 317.6 Tm (3. The delay varies slightly between individuals and tasks: faster decisions \(well-) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 54 305.6 Tm (practiced tasks\) have higher r \(stronger recurrent connections from training\),) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 54 293.6 Tm (producing shorter buildup times. This is observed experimentally.) Tj T* ET
BT /F3 10 Tf 12 TL ET
BT 1 0 0 1 54 281.6 Tm (4. The delay does not imply epiphenomenalism: consciousness is not a passive) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 54 269.6 Tm (observer watching pre-made decisions. It is the phase transition itself. The) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 54 257.6 Tm ("decision" does not exist as a unified state until coherence crosses C_min. Before) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 54 245.6 Tm (that, there are local neural activations that correlate with the eventual decision) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 54 233.6 Tm (but do not constitute it.) Tj T* ET
